article.description: Kristi Toliver had 24 points and eight assists in her return from a one-game suspension and Maryland (No. 16 ESPN/USA Today; No. 14 AP) beat Mississippi State 80-73 in the finals of the Terrapin Classic. It was the Bulldogs' first defeat of the season.
article.headline: Maryland wins final of Terrapin Classic
article.linkText: Maryland hands Miss. State first loss of season
article.story:
COLLEGE PARK, Md. -- Kristi Toliver had 24 points and eight assists in her return from a one-game suspension and Maryland (No. 16 ESPN/USA Today; No. 14 AP) beat Mississippi State 80-73 in the finals of the Terrapin Classic. It was the Bulldogs' first defeat of the season.

Demauria Liles and Marah Strickland scored 16 points apiece for the Terrapins (11-2). They have won four straight and 11 of 12.

Alexis Rack led Mississippi State (11-1) with 24 points, and Robin Porter and Tysheka Grimes had 10 each. The Bulldogs' 11-0 start matched the best in school history. They have dropped eight consecutive games to ranked opponents.

Toliver sat out Monday's semifinal victory over UNC Asheville for violating a team rule.
